  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We present evidence for the existence of a quantum lower bound on the Bekenstein–Hawking temperature of black holes. The suggested bound is supported by a gedanken experiment in which a charged particle is dropped into a Kerr black hole. It is proved that the temperature of the final Kerr–Newman black-hole configuration is bounded from below by the relation <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>BH</mtext></mrow></msub><mo>×</mo><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>H</mtext></mrow></msub><mo>></mo><msup><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>ħ</mi><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>H</mtext></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math> , where <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>H</mtext></mrow></msub></math> is the horizon radius of the black hole.</subfield>
