  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="m">Note that the limiting case <math altimg="si92.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>c</mtext></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>μ</mi></math> corresponds to a charged spherical object whose rest mass μ is attributed exclusively to the electrostatic self-energy it produces [8,9]. The factor of 1/2 in (7) comes from the assumption that the electric charge is uniformly spread on a thin spherical shell</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
    <subfield code="o">10</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="h">Eling, C.</subfield>
