  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="m">Interestingly, it was shown in [28] that the (weaker version [28] of the) hoop conjecture must be invoked in order to guarantee the validity of the generalized second law of thermodynamics [3] in a gedanken experiment in which an entropy bearing object is lowered slowly into a near-extremal black hole</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
    <subfield code="o">29</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="m">We shall henceforth assume that the original Kerr black hole is a near-extremal one</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
    <subfield code="o">30</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="m">As discussed above, this new (and larger) horizon is expected to be formed according to the original hoop conjecture [24] and its generalized version (19)</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
    <subfield code="o">31</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="m">We recall that the proper radius of the charged spherical body is given by <math altimg="si104.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>min</mtext></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>μ</mi></math> [see Eq. (7)]</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
    <subfield code="o">32</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="m">It is important to emphasize that our assumption <math altimg="si96.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msubsup><mrow><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow><mrow><mtext>min</mtext></mrow></msubsup><mo>≪</mo><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow></msub></math> corresponds to particles in the regime <math altimg="si105.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>μ</mi><mo>≪</mo><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo></mrow></msub></math> [see Eq. (23)]</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
    <subfield code="o">33</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="h">Unruh, W.G.</subfield>
